  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering Environmental Education in 14 schools</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to ensure in perpetuity the conservation of the Volcanoes National Park  rich biodiversity resources include threatened mountain gorillas through strengthening of environmental outreach education programs in schools. The project will be implemented in 2 to 3 pilot Schools of each of Musanze, Burera, Nyabihu and Rubavu Districts. The project will assist in creation of environmental awareness through school outreach programs.</narrative>
  </description>
